DNS-over-HTTPS Debian Package
==============================

This package provides DNS-over-HTTPS client and server implementation.

Components:
-----------
- doh-client: Local DNS proxy that queries upstream DoH servers
- doh-server: DoH server that forwards to traditional DNS servers

Quick Start:
------------

For DoH Client (most common use case):
  1. Disable systemd-resolved: sudo doh-resolve disable
  2. Configure client: sudo nano /etc/dns-over-https/doh-client.conf
  3. Start service: sudo systemctl start doh-client
  4. Test: dig @127.0.0.1 google.com

For DoH Server:
  1. Configure server: sudo nano /etc/dns-over-https/doh-server.conf
  2. Set up reverse proxy (Apache/Nginx/Caddy)
  3. Start service: sudo systemctl start doh-server

Documentation:
--------------
See /usr/share/doc/dns-over-https/README.md for complete documentation.

Upstream: https://github.com/m13253/dns-over-https
